        "### Discovery D — Does content age relate to trend direction?\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's examine how the `trend_direction` of content (whether it's `up`, `down`, `stable`, `flat`, or `new`) is influenced by its `content_age_days`."
      ],
      "id": "0aff2056"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 529
        },
        "id": "b2a02c96",
        "outputId": "23821f1b-fa32-45fd-babc-ab8a00e14e68"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Define age bins for content_age_days\n",
        "age_bins = [0, 30, 90, 180, 365, 730, np.inf] # 0-30 days, 31-90 days, etc.\n",
        "age_labels = ['<1M', '1-3M', '3-6M', '6-12M', '1-2Y', '>2Y']\n",
        "\n",
        "df['content_age_group'] = pd.cut(df['content_age_days'], bins=age_bins, labels=age_labels, right=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate the proportion of each trend_direction within each age group\n",
        "age_trend_distribution = df.groupby('content_age_group')['trend_direction'].value_counts(normalize=True).unstack(fill_value=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the distribution\n",
        "print(age_trend_distribution.round(3).to_string())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Visualize the distribution\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "ax = age_trend_distribution.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "plt.title('Trend Direction Distribution by Content Age Group')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Content Age Group')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Proportion')\n",
        "plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')\n",
        "plt.legend(title='Trend Direction', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nObservation: Younger content (e.g., '<1M') tends to have a higher proportion of 'new' trend direction, which is expected. As content ages, the proportion of 'stable' and 'flat' trends seems to increase, while 'up' and 'down' trends become more prominent in older content groups, indicating dynamic performance over time. This suggests that content age can be a factor in predicting its trend direction, but the relationship is complex and not purely linear.\")"
      ],
